Perhaps instead of hating, y’all should start studying and copying and learning from @loganpaul & @jakepaul & @floydmayweather.
.
It’s easy to be an armchair quarterback. It’s easy to sit in the shadows playing it safe and making no dents in the universe. But we don’t build statues for the dudes in the cheap seats.
.
Hats off to @loganpaul, you inspired me last night my man. You went 8 rounds with one of the best ever. You did the work and did something very few humans will ever do. I was smiling ear to ear from your walkout to your after fight words. You are an inspiration and motivation to many. Keep going my brother.
.
🚀

You and I have been conditioned to LIE. Ever since we were kids our parents, schooling, societal influence and religion has conditioned and programmed us to lie... To play it safe... To not say things that might make others uncomfortable... Want to know why so many people stay broke? Partly because of work ethic, but a main reason is because you fear the judgements of those closest to you... If you grew up on a broke family you fear the family saying “do you think you are better than us?” “Do you think you are above us?” It’s fascinating... We are taught to dream and live but PROGRAMMED to play small, live small, and LIE about what we really want... “I WANT TO BE AN ASTRONAUT” then they’d chuckle and say “be practical.” So what did you do??? You quit dreaming and most of all, YOU STARTED SECOND GUESSING YOURSELF AND SAYING SAFE SHIT, NOT THE TRUTH!!!
.
The guy in this video grew up poor and lived in a small town. He didn’t make much money and instead of saying what he really wanted because he’d be judged for making MORE MONEY, he lied... Fast forward... He’s now making far above $200,000 cause he quit LYING and build what HE wanted.
.
🚀

.

.
Find your sweet spot.
.
Swing at those pitches.
.
Get on base.
.
💰

.
Proud of you bubba! GOOD WORK!
.
A little side note on this video... I recently showed him one of my favorite wrestling moves called the cross face cradle. I told him when you go across a guys face make sure that he knows that you’re there and doesn’t forget it. 😉You can see him doing that pretty intensely in this video! 🤣 I had to remind him after the match that we’re not doing MMA and throwing punches and to make sure there’s a little less wind up in those cross faces next time. 😉

node.text:
Remember when we were kids playing on the playground and the bully would try and take kids lunch money? Some kids got scared of the bully. Some kids got intimidated by the bully. Some kids got humiliated by the bully and didn’t wanna deal with it anymore so they just gave the bully their money.... Day after day, the bully knew the weak ones and he picked on them over and over, getting their lunch money AND some.... Then one day that one kid told the bully to piss off and punched him in the face.... Guess what happened? That kid didn’t give his money to the bully, and the bully never tried to take his (or anyone else’s) money again.
.
Remember this when you put the ‘CLOSED’ sign in the front window of your business you were “forced” to close.
.
God Bless 🇺🇸

Remember when we were kids playing on the playground and the bully would try and take kids lunch money? Some kids got scared of the bully. Some kids got intimidated by the bully. Some kids got humiliated by the bully and didn’t wanna deal with it anymore so they just gave the bully their money.... Day after day, the bully knew the weak ones and he picked on them over and over, getting their lunch money AND some.... Then one day that one kid told the bully to piss off and punched him in the face.... Guess what happened? That kid didn’t give his money to the bully, and the bully never tried to take his (or anyone else’s) money again.
.
Remember this when you put the ‘CLOSED’ sign in the front window of your business you were “forced” to close.
.
God Bless 🇺🇸

Yesterday we hosted the first LIONS DEN BUSINESS MASTERMIND FLY-IN at my HQ in Salt Lake.
.
This is a one day event where 40 people came in from all over the country to meet and discuss every facet of business and life growth.
.
Men and Women from every walk of life. A client who just exited his company for $20,000,000. Owners and operators of businesses. Landscapers, gym owners, restauranteurs, coaches, tech managers, E-commerce sellers, real estate investors, custom home builders, excavation company owner, investors, SEO specialists, web developers.
.
It was a mixed bag of folks building not only rad businesses, but folks who want to optimize their life.
.
I love these days when we all get together, eliminate the pride and ego and just get down to business on making more while working less, building and scaling, and most of all adding value to everyone else in the room and choosing to live an epic life.
.
I know you’ve heard this but who you hang and associate with matters. Who you take counsel and advice form matters. Who you spend time with matters.
.
Some major shit happened yesterday for everyone in attendance. I think a lot of y’all would be really surprised how dramatically your life can change in just a few hours when you are in an room of winners who truly want you to win.
.
This was the first FLY-IN hosted for members of THE LIONS DEN (my coaching group) and it was a major success. We will be doing A LOT more of these. I may even open them up to the general public at some point in time, but for now they are just another incredible value add for members of my tribe in THE LIONS DEN.
.
Get around good people. Network with successful people. Ask better questions. Listen more. Most of all GO ALL IN on yourself, INVEST IN YOURSELF and watch how rapidly your life changes.
.
👊🏼

You value what you invest in.
.
You invest in what you value.
.
I value my wife and our marriage greatly.
.
So weekly date night is NOT negotiable.
.
Last night I made reservations at our favorite spot and secretly booked a room to spend the night.
.
When I told her the plans yesterday morning she reminded me that I had 40 clients coming to town today for our first ‘Lions Den Fly In’ so staying the night might be tough. (Yea, I have severe ADHD/ADD and things like forgetting big events or filling up with gas happen 🤷🏻‍♂️).
.
I was gonna cancel the room but we both looked at each other with a smirk and knew what was up 😉.
.
All day yesterday she was texting me next level sexy wife shit, telling me what she was gonna do to me and what she wanted me to do to her. (Perhaps that’s why I completely spaced getting gas 😜.
.
We did dinner, we checked into our cabin, we had mind bending sex, we sat under the stars talking and we were home by midnight.
.
Fellas it ain’t about where you go or what you do, it’s about being proactive and investing. It’s about making her and your marriage a priority. It’s about not just winging it, it’s actually giving a fuck and making her feel that’s she’s special. It’s showing the hell up and SHOWING her she’s special.
.
We take time to do due diligence on deals, to check markets and charts, to build marketing and sales channels, we spend a lot of time and dedicated energy on investing our money and building wealth, we need to do the same with our queen and family.
.
I promise you it’ll pay significantly larger dividends than any market or asset or coin ever will.
.
👊🏼

I love this woman. Yea some days I want to leave her at the gas station, but the truth is even if I did I’d flip around and go get her 🤣. Might take a day or two but I’d for sure come back.
.
She’s always hugging me and telling me nice things. She knows when I’m grumpy and she keeps hugging me and telling me nice things regardless. She’s a great cook and a thoughtful mom.
.
Know what I love about her the most? This little kid she turns into. The little giggly voice and the antics. I’ve loved this about her from the very beginning. Even when shit goes sideways, she’s got this innocent little kid that comes out and I love it. It makes me smile and every time I fall for her even more.
.
Shes sweet and she’s caring. If you’ve met her you know what I mean. She really gives a fuck about people. She’s definitely a boss and she will fuck some shit up, but after she smacks ya around she will smile and hug you.
.
I love the little shit in life more and more. The mornings in bed. The date nights just walking around together. The dinners and sunsets on the back deck. The test drives of the new car and how she tries to use the clapper 👏 to turn the car off.
.
I love you momma. Thanks for being you. Change lots, but never change.❤️

.
And how you are “FULL OF YOURSELF.”
.
Hear me y’all.
.
FUCK THOSE PEOPLE!
.
GET THEM OUT OF YOUR LIFE!
.
CUT THEM ALL OFF!
.
You worked to get where you are! You fought the demons! You paid the price! You did what they didn’t and wouldn’t do, so FUCK THEM!
.
If you’re reading this right now and you’re battling with the fear and intimidation of GROWING and being labeled shit that small minded people like to label, and you have any respect at all for me, hear these words.
.
FUCK THOSE PEOPLE.
.
GET UP AND WIN.
.
WIN REALLY FUCKING BIG!
.
A winner will NEVER tell you to be “humble” or that you’re a “narcissist”, these are labels LOSERS use.
.
Remember that shit.
.
Remember this when you have the ball and you’re standing in the end zone.
.
SPIKE THAT MOTHER FUCKER AND SPIKE IT BIG!
.
👊🏼

node.text:
Dads. 

You have to SHOW THEM. 

You have to SHOW THEM you living your dreams. 

You have to SHOW THEM how a woman should be treated. 

You have to SHOW THEM tenacity. 

You have to SHOW THEM you keeping your word. 

You have to SHOW THEM your tears. 

You have to SHOW THEM your testimony. 

I spent many years telling my kids how things should be, how dreams should look, how man should stand, how love should feel, what happiness will be like, and what it’ll be like WHEN I get here or there. 

I was doing it wrong. 

I believe I went through that experience so I could truly understand not only what my kids needed, but how I needed to mature. 

So much pressure is put on fathers. 

So many influences. 

From family. 
From church. 
From ourselves!

Perhaps how mom and dad or the neighbors did it is the exact opposite of how you’re supposed to do it?

Doesn’t make them wrong or bad, but my father raised me the best he knew how. 

I know what I experienced as a kid and not having a single memory of a guys night, guys trip, or even a shared interest is forefront in my mind as I navigate the role of father, and which is why I’m so deeply committed to my role as father, and to doing these things with my children. 

I can’t predict the future but I’m a betting man and I bet in 30 years my son talks to his kids about how he raced the Baja 1000 when he was 11, or how he camped with his dad. 

I bet when he’s older and he’s faced with a scary situation what’s called to his mind is how he watched his dad do scary things. 

There ain’t a rule book for this father thing, but one thing I’m 100% certain of is this. 

I don’t remember a lot of what my dad told me,

But I remember what he SHOWED ME.

Dads, SHOW THEM.

🙏

I love that so many of y’all support our company LIONS NOT SHEEP.
.
We just ran a promotion to get an autographed hat and we sold 334 hats in 12 hours. Today I signed every single one of them. Makes me proud as hell to know that these hats are going to humans that support and love this country as much as I do and that this message of standing as a LION is spreading.
.
Building this brand and this company has been incredible. I’ve connected to so many amazing people around the globe. It’s also stretched me to become a better leader, business owner, father, son and lover. I believe how you do one thing is how you do all things, so I’m not surprised as I’ve grown personally that this company has grown. LIONS NOT SHEEP started as a personal mantra for me. My personal declaration to stand as a LION and not follow blindly as a sheep, and to know this mantra is now many others mantra, and to see it ripple the universe as it has, is humbling.
.
Thank you to all who support us. Thank you to all of you who support me personally. I wake up every day grateful for another day and I’ll never not be grateful for these days, for this business, or for the opportunity to grow.
.
Much love y’all.
.
🦁
